# Example Cron Configuration for Automated Secret Rotation
#
# This file provides example cron schedules for automated challenge token
# secret rotation. Copy and customise for your deployment environment.
#
# Installation:
#   1. Copy this file:
#        cp scripts/cron-rotation.example /etc/cron.d/prompt-hash-rotation
#   2. Set the required environment variables (see below).
#   3. Adjust the schedule and paths for your deployment.
#   4. Ensure the script is executable:
#        chmod +x scripts/rotate-secrets.sh
#
# Required environment variables:
#   ADMIN_ROTATION_TOKEN  — Bearer token authorising the rotation endpoint.
#                           Must be ≥16 characters. Recommended: 32+ hex chars.
#                           Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
#   UNLOCK_SERVICE_URL    — Base URL of the unlock service, e.g.
#                           https://your-domain.com
#
# Tip: store these in /etc/environment (system-wide) or in a secured
# environment file loaded by your cron daemon / systemd service rather than
# placing them directly in this file.
#
# Security Recommendations:
#   - Always run --dry-run first and review the output before scheduling.
#   - Rotate secrets every 30–90 days (see table in docs/secret-rotation.md).
#   - Use longer grace periods (10–15 min) during high-traffic windows.
#   - Monitor rotation logs and alert on failure.
#   - Never commit real token values to version control.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Environment — set via /etc/environment or your deployment platform.
# Uncomment and fill in if your cron daemon does not inherit these.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ADMIN_ROTATION_TOKEN=<generate with: openssl rand -hex 32>
# UNLOCK_SERVICE_URL=https://your-domain.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DRY-RUN — run this manually before enabling the scheduled rotation.
# Validates all env vars and reports what would happen without any mutation.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# /path/to/prompt-hash-stellar/scripts/rotate-secrets.sh \
#   --dry-run \
#   --env staging \
#   >> /var/log/secret-rotation.log 2>&1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Scheduled rotations — uncomment exactly ONE of the lines below.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Rotate every 30 days at 02:00 UTC (standard production)
# 0 2 1 * * /path/to/prompt-hash-stellar/scripts/rotate-secrets.sh --grace-period 600 --env production >> /var/log/secret-rotation.log 2>&1

# Rotate every 60 days at 03:00 UTC (moderate-risk environments)
# 0 3 1 */2 * /path/to/prompt-hash-stellar/scripts/rotate-secrets.sh --grace-period 900 --env production >> /var/log/secret-rotation.log 2>&1

# Rotate every 90 days at 04:00 UTC (lowest frequency)
# 0 4 1 */3 * /path/to/prompt-hash-stellar/scripts/rotate-secrets.sh --grace-period 600 --env production >> /var/log/secret-rotation.log 2>&1

# Weekly rotation — for high-security environments
# 0 2 * * 0 /path/to/prompt-hash-stellar/scripts/rotate-secrets.sh --grace-period 300 --env production >> /var/log/secret-rotation.log 2>&1
